/div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WzMKa7c</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HorrorMango]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Compilation of noted voter fraud in Georgia</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TgSHGMn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/exNQVwZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1. Ballot Staffing (To Cancel Station): 
When GD (georgian dream pro-russia party) failed to score a victory in a particular station, they staffed the ballot box with multiple ballots demonstrably so that the station would get cancelled. This is Marneuli precinct, it was closed following ballot-stuffing evidence.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mOyRVu1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2. Violation of secrecy of vote:
Sometimes a camera was directed at the voting booth, the boxes were not sealed, and nearly all ballots revealed whom the voter had chosen. Both authorized and unauthorized individuals accompanied voters into the booth.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xvf5yo9.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>3. Physical violence:
Physical violence occurred against observers, journalists, and ordinary citizens both inside and outside the precincts. Mobsters were mobilized in vehicles near the precincts.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Vqsp60i.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>4. The opposition representatives and commission members were assaulted.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aEURZA6.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5. Non-authorized persons and chaos in the precincts:
Resulting in chaos and disorder, providing a perfect opportunity for ballot stuffing and other forms of electoral fraud. These individuals often initiated quarrels inside the precinct and directed voters inside the booths.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0Ieltav.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>6. Two Ballots: 
Some govt. affiliated people received two ballots.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yarl6Rn.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>7. Disregard of Marking Procedures: 
There were many instances of marking liquid being NOT being applied, being removed, and/or UV-Light device malfunction.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xe4UOo0.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>8. Bribery: 
Multiple well-documented cases of bribery; giving people various amounts of money as an incentive to vote for the ruling regime.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gZRncvf.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>9. Hindering the observers: 
Election observers were hindered in their observations, not allowed to move freely (or at all) within the precincts, physically blocked, instructed not to look at the verification apparatus, inking checks, or inking procedures,</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ykDO5NL.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>10. Errors in the voter lists:
There were multiple errors in the voter lists at the electoral precincts, either including the names of deceased persons or omitting individuals who were directed to vote at that precinct.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UtU3wKx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>11. Device malfunctions:
Electronic devices often malfunctioned.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/x38t7OB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>12. Counting invalid ballots:
Invalid ballots were always counted in favor of GD. In some instances, valid ballots that should have counted for the opposition were marked as invalid.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pPJuSjd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>13. Agitators with voters' lists:
